Package: pep725
Title: PEP725 Pan-European Phenological Data Analysis
Version: 0.0.0.901
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Matthias", "Templ", , "matthias.templ@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8638-5276")),
      person("Barbara", "Templ", , "barbara.a.templ@gmail.com", role = c("aut"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-9391-5888"))
           )
Description: Provides comprehensive tools for analyzing phenological data from
    the PEP725 Pan-European Phenology Database (Templ et al. 2018)
    <doi:10.1007/s00484-018-1512-8> and other European sources. Core analytical
    functions include calculation of phenological normals (climate baselines),
    anomaly detection, elevation and latitude gradient analysis, and spatial
    synchrony assessment. The package supports data import from PEP725 files,
    synthetic data generation for testing and teaching, and downloadable example
    datasets. Visualization capabilities include interactive 'leaflet' maps for
    station selection, static maps via 'ggmap', and trend plots with robust
    regression. Integration with climate data (NASA GISS temperature anomalies,
    MeteoSwiss) enables climate-phenology relationship analysis. Quality
    assessment tools help identify reliable observation series.
